Heat the olive oil in a pan over a medium heat. Fry the onion and garlic for 4-5 minutes, or until softened, stirring occasionally.Add the chopped chicken to the pan and fry for 4-5 minutes, or until golden-brown, stirring occasionally. Add the tomato pur√©e and chicken stock and heat until simmering.Stir in the tomatoes and chickpeas and continue to simmer for 2-3 minutes.To serve, spoon the chicken and sauce onto a plate and crumble over the garlic-and-herb cream cheese.